-- Kazakhstan May Start Refinery Construction Next Year, IFX Says
-- B y   N a r i m a n   G i z i t d i n o v
-- 2012-12-13T13:57:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-13/kazakhstan-may-start-refinery-construction-next-year-ifx-says.html
TOO Kazenergoregion plans to start
construction of an 8 billion-euro ($10.5 billion) oil refinery
in northern  Kazakhstan  next year, Interfax reported.  The closely held company will invest 2 billion euros in an
initial phase at the planned plant in Bulaevo, Interfax reported
today, citing a company official.  The refinery will process as much as 6 million metric tons
of crude a year at first and 12 million tons of oil when the
second phase is completed, Interfax reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nariman Gizitdinov in Almaty at 
 ngizitdinov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  